    <h3>Feature Goals</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Inline drop down which shows some of the available choices to enter.</li>
        <li>Ability to have two calendars side by side for start/end dates</li>
        <li>New match: "two weeks from tomorrow", "one month from last monday", "1 year from (next\s)?friday"</li>
				<li>New match: "the day after tomorrow", "the day before yesterday"</li>
    	<li>New match: "first monday in november" </li>
    	<li>New match: "2nd wed in dec" </li>
    	<li>Initial date validation with server side code (Ruby/PHP/etc) to ensure that the base date used via their time zone is correct.</li>
    	<li>If a date is not matched, then use an AJAX extension/plugin (Ruby/PHP/etc) to try and make sense of it 
    	   <ul>
            <li>Utilize <a href="http://runt.rubyforge.org/">RUNT</a> as the third party tool for Ruby</li>
    	   </ul>
      </li>
    	<li>Second or even inline box to enter the Time with same text based functionality
    		<ul>
    			<li>Match: [all date matches] at 7pm</li>
    			<li>Match: [all date matches] @ 7pm</li>
    			<li>Match: 4am</li>
    			<li>Match: 18:00</li>
    			<li>Match: (1|one) hour[s]?</li>
    			<li>Match: (5|five) min(ute[s]?)?</li>
    			<li>Match: morning (return 9am - configurable time)</li>
    			<li>Match: evening (return 5pm - configurable time)</li>
    			<li>Match: now</li>
    		</ul>
    	</li>
    	<li>Have a suggestion? Please do <a href="http://nshb.net/contact.html">email me</a></li>
    </ul>
    
